# Explorer Refactor Boundaries

- Keep `useExplorer.js` as a React composition hook. Move navigation, scan session, workspace session, and bridge-registration logic into focused modules instead of adding more responsibilities to the hook.
- Extract non-React explorer workflow helpers into `src/viewer/explorer/`. These modules should not import React.
  - `explorer-navigation.js` owns file navigation orchestration, history/hash/title/focus updates, and tree reveal/reuse decisions.
  - `explorer-scan-session.js` owns AbortController scan sessions and sibling scan runner/fallback behavior.
  - `explorer-workspace-session.js` owns workspace open/restore/exit workflows for file-listing roots, directory handles, and webkit virtual files.
- Keep React-only adapters under `src/viewer/react/hooks/explorer/`.
  - `useExplorerBridgeRegistration.js` owns bridge mutation for `navigateToFile` and `virtualFileExists`.
  - `useExplorerActions.js` owns action callbacks returned to `ExplorerPanel`.
- Use dependency injection for browser/runtime side effects in extracted helpers (`bridge`, `sendMessage`, `document`, `window`, callbacks) where it keeps logic testable.
- Preserve the existing explorer bridge contract: `navigateToFile` and `virtualFileExists` are assigned by the hook and cleared on cleanup.
- Preserve workspace virtual-file behavior and `MDP_WS_FILE` handling. Do not convert virtual workspace files into `file:` URLs.
- Add or update focused tests for pure navigation decisions, scan cancellation, and tree reveal behavior before changing implementation-heavy paths.
- Sibling scans use `AbortController`; abort on teardown, workspace switch/open, mode changes, and explicit progress cancellation.
